It's time to destroy our bedroom. The last room in the house where, apart from a bit of decorating, nothing has been done.
The ugly electric fireplace and the hearth must go. We need to rebuild the fireplace, replace the chipped plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
We found a few dead birds in the back of the chimney, very dried out :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche has turned out well
Here comes a new wardrobe (but we haven't even started on the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heating!
And we even thought about installing this nice little vent, so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlay is in place, I have made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be laid. We are having a tea break right now
Buhu. Today is going slowly because of super complicated cuts around the doorposts, so that we have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be relaid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Done, but at the end! The crowning achievement was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. Tonight we will sleep well!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator will come in a month, so we currently have raw plaster style
A bit more DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel the lower sections around the doorposts, where the floor will then fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then out at 5 o'clock in the morning to pick up Item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and final sprint in the hallway, the baseboards are installed. Joints will be made once the adhesive is dry
